posts.name: Aiden Townsend
posts.cooked: If you mean to set a power for one motor and the other motor does the same thing, there’s a follow method. You can run motor1.follow(motor2); in the setup code. Whatever you do to motor2 will be done to motor1. You could also have a set(double power) method which takes the single power and sets it to both motors.
